I" 	<p>The <code>metoffice</code> weather platform uses the Met Officeâ€™s <a href="https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/datapoint">DataPoint API</a> for weather data.</p>
<h2>Configuration</h2>
<p>To add the Met Office weather platform to your installation, youâ€™ll need to register for a free API key at the link above and then add the following to your <code>configuration.yaml</code> file:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Example configuration.yaml entry
weather:
  - platform: metoffice
    api_key: YOUR_API_KEY
</code></pre>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='api_key' href='#api_key'></a> api_key</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>Your personal API key from the <a href="https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/datapoint">Datapoint website</a>.</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='name' href='#name'></a> name</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>Additional name for the weather integration in Home Assistant.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p>Met Office</p>
</p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='latitude' href='#latitude'></a> latitude</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='float'>float</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Inclusive)</span><span class='description'><p>Latitude coordinate to monitor weather of (required if <strong>longitude</strong> is specified), defaults to coordinates defined in your <code>configuration.yaml</code>.</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='longitude' href='#longitude'></a> longitude</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='float'>float</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Inclusive)</span><span class='description'><p>Longitude coordinate to monitor weather of (required if <strong>latitude</strong> is specified), defaults to coordinates defined in your <code>configuration.yaml</code>.</p>
</span></p></dd></dl>
</div>
<div class='note'>
<p>This platform is an alternative to the <a href="/integrations/sensor.metoffice/"><code>metoffice</code></a> sensor.
The weather platform is easier to configure but less customizable.</p>
